WEBVTT

00:03.000 --> 00:04.040
Previously on "How To Get Away
With Murder"...

00:04.040 --> 00:05.290
Get married in a church.
They're cheap.

00:05.290 --> 00:06.710
Hey, Dad. It's me. I wanted
to talk about the wedding.

00:06.710 --> 00:08.540
I'd never hit on you knowing
it hasn't been that long

00:08.540 --> 00:10.040
since what happened
to Wes.
You know about Wes?

00:10.040 --> 00:11.420
Don't talk to me
anymore.

00:11.420 --> 00:13.460
Bonnie: You ripped open
the part of my life

00:13.460 --> 00:15.580
that I killed myself
to get past.

00:15.580 --> 00:18.170
What can I do?
You did what you did.

00:18.170 --> 00:19.710
I want you and I
to work together

00:19.710 --> 00:22.380
to create the Pennsylvania
Fair Defense Project.

00:22.380 --> 00:23.750
Stay. Please.

00:23.750 --> 00:25.750
I promise I will have your back
at every turn.

00:25.750 --> 00:28.040
The Board agreed
to free Nathaniel Lahey.

00:28.040 --> 00:29.380
You just need
to accept the job.

00:29.380 --> 00:30.960
I have Ms. Keating
in my office.

00:30.960 --> 00:32.080
Please relieve her
of her badge.

00:32.080 --> 00:33.540
She no longer works here.

00:33.540 --> 00:35.000
Woman: I'm afraid
there's been an incident.

00:35.000 --> 00:36.250
What does that mean?
Incident?

00:36.250 --> 00:39.500
♪♪

00:40.790 --> 00:42.920
[ Birds chirping ]

00:42.920 --> 00:45.040
[ Cellphone ringing, vibrating ]

00:49.250 --> 00:51.330
[ Coughs ]

00:51.330 --> 00:53.790
[ Ringing and vibrating
continue ]

00:53.790 --> 00:55.080
[ Cellphone beeps ]

01:01.540 --> 01:03.500
[ Gasps ]

01:03.500 --> 01:05.500
Good morning.
I'm Dr. Maureen Groff,

01:05.500 --> 01:07.830
Chief Medical Officer
of Philadelphia.

01:07.830 --> 01:10.920
Over the past month,
my office has been conducting

01:10.920 --> 01:13.920
an investigation into the death
of Nathaniel Lahey Senior,

01:13.920 --> 01:16.460
a 71-year-old inmate.

01:16.460 --> 01:19.250
On the night in question,
Mr. Lahey was escorted

01:19.250 --> 01:21.790
by two correctional officers
from his cell.

01:21.790 --> 01:24.380
They were to transport him
to Wilson Park Hospital.

01:24.380 --> 01:27.420
When Officer Gladden
uncuffed the inmate

01:27.420 --> 01:29.170
and attempted to take a letter
he had written,

01:29.170 --> 01:31.330
Mr. Lahey became agitated.

01:31.330 --> 01:33.500
A struggle ensued,
during which

01:33.500 --> 01:36.500
Mr. Lahey took a pencil
he was holding

01:36.500 --> 01:39.960
and stabbed Officer Gladden
in her right leg.

01:39.960 --> 01:42.960
Mr. Lahey then reached
for her gun.

01:42.960 --> 01:46.500
Officer Wagner
fired one shot at Mr. Lahey,

01:46.500 --> 01:48.170
striking his frontal skull.

01:48.170 --> 01:51.960
Mr. Lahey died instantly
on contact.

01:51.960 --> 01:53.460
And there was gunshot residue
present on his forehead...

01:53.460 --> 01:55.120
Do you have a minute?
I need your signature
on these plea memos.

01:55.120 --> 01:56.500
...both indications that
he was shot at close range...

01:56.500 --> 01:58.330
Hey, are you watching this?
I mean, you should be,

01:58.330 --> 02:00.250
at least if you want
your blood to boil.
...as indicated in
Officer Wagner's statement.

02:00.250 --> 02:02.290
Millstone, can you
go get me a coffee?
He fired the gun...

02:02.290 --> 02:03.960
I just got you one.

02:03.960 --> 02:05.580
...before the deceased could
grab Officer Gladden's firearm.

02:05.580 --> 02:07.580
Mr. Lahey
additionally suffered...
Right, Boss.

02:07.580 --> 02:09.750
...a postmortem
blunt-force injury...

02:09.750 --> 02:10.790
[ Door opens ]
...to his anterior skull...

02:10.790 --> 02:13.210
I'm fine.

02:13.210 --> 02:14.750
I just want
to prepare you.
...as a result
of falling backwards.

02:14.750 --> 02:16.080
We observed no other notable
external injuries.

02:16.080 --> 02:18.250
Nate's planning on coming back
to work this week.

02:18.250 --> 02:20.250
Any imbalance or alteration...
Good for him.

02:20.250 --> 02:22.670
...could have caused
this behavioral disruption.

02:22.670 --> 02:24.620
Multiple attempts to calm him
were unsuccessful.
I'm sad for him, obviously,

02:24.620 --> 02:27.000
but I also
still get to be pissed.

02:27.000 --> 02:28.790
When questioned about
Mr. Lahey's state of mind

02:28.790 --> 02:31.040
during the time
leading up to the incident,

02:31.040 --> 02:34.080
both officers described
Mr. Lahey's behavior

02:34.080 --> 02:36.080
as wild-eyed
and volatile.

02:36.080 --> 02:38.580
Unfortunately,
there were no other witnesses

02:38.580 --> 02:40.790
to verify
the officers' account,

02:40.790 --> 02:43.500
and the surveillance cameras
outside the prison

02:43.500 --> 02:44.500
malfunctioned that night.

02:44.500 --> 02:45.920
Maintenance records show...

02:45.920 --> 02:47.920
this was a common occurrence...
It's called a cover-up,
or are you in on it, too?

02:47.920 --> 02:49.460
...in this section
of the prison.
You know she can't hear you.

02:49.460 --> 02:50.790
God can hear us.

02:50.790 --> 02:53.000
She better damn well send
all these people to hell.

02:53.000 --> 02:54.500
Well, maybe that's something
Connor and I

02:54.500 --> 02:56.750
can ask the minister to make
happen during our meeting later.

02:56.750 --> 02:59.420
No, I am too depressed to be
pretend religious today.

02:59.420 --> 03:01.210
Amen.
You know how hard
it was to find

03:01.210 --> 03:02.710
a wedding venue
last minute?

03:02.710 --> 03:04.250
So we go, smile,

03:04.250 --> 03:05.830
and say we're all about
the good Lord.

03:05.830 --> 03:08.000
Two separate
toxicology screens

03:08.000 --> 03:09.670
were performed
on the deceased.

03:09.670 --> 03:13.330
Neither Zyprexa nor lithium
were found in his system,

03:13.330 --> 03:15.080
even though
he'd been prescribed

03:15.080 --> 03:18.120
both anti-psychotic drugs
several months prior.

03:18.120 --> 03:20.170
This evidence suggests

03:20.170 --> 03:23.000
Mr. Lahey stopped
taking his medications,

03:23.000 --> 03:24.960
a possible cause
of his behavior

03:24.960 --> 03:26.540
the night of his death.
Bull.

03:26.540 --> 03:28.170
As Mr. Lahey had a long history
of mental illness...

03:28.170 --> 03:29.920
Your first
interview's here.
Send her in.

03:29.920 --> 03:32.500
In conclusion,
due to witness accounts

03:32.500 --> 03:36.210
and the exemplary service
records of both officers,

03:36.210 --> 03:38.210
it is my office's conclusion

03:38.210 --> 03:41.080
that the manner
of Mr. Lahey's death

03:41.080 --> 03:44.330
was not due
to criminal negligence

03:44.330 --> 03:47.670
but was rather
a justifiable homicide.

03:47.670 --> 03:51.710
This investigation
is hereby officially closed.

03:51.710 --> 03:56.790
♪♪

03:56.790 --> 04:01.880
♪♪

04:01.880 --> 04:04.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:08.420 --> 04:10.790
The Dispatch and The Voice
are gonna keep digging,

04:10.790 --> 04:13.330
doing stories every day.

04:13.330 --> 04:15.500
And I'm gonna push
for an inquest.

04:15.500 --> 04:16.670
They don't
even do inquests

04:16.670 --> 04:19.000
on cops who shoot kids
on playgrounds.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.080
We fought too hard
for him to give up now,

04:21.080 --> 04:22.620
especially with the Governor
on our side.

04:24.620 --> 04:26.580
You still think
she's on our side?

04:26.580 --> 04:30.040
I'll beat her ass
if she's not.

04:30.040 --> 04:33.170
TV Reporter:
It's a tragic end to the life
of Nathaniel Lahey Senior,

04:33.170 --> 04:34.830
a man whose life's story
shed light

04:34.830 --> 04:37.330
on the ills
of solitary confinement.

04:37.330 --> 04:38.830
Many also thought his
Supreme Court case decision...
What morons thought that?

04:38.830 --> 04:40.460
...ruled that the issue

04:40.460 --> 04:42.620
of ineffective assistance
of counsel

04:42.620 --> 04:45.120
is systematic and needs
to be nationally addressed

04:45.120 --> 04:46.290
with more robust funding.

04:46.290 --> 04:48.290
Should I
get you some popcorn?

04:48.290 --> 04:50.460
Are you sure
you can't zoom in closer?

04:50.460 --> 04:52.040
[ Sighs ]
What for?

04:52.040 --> 04:53.040
Wanna count
his abs?

04:53.040 --> 04:54.540
Look at that Post-it
on his desk.

04:54.540 --> 04:56.250
It could be a list
of his passwords.

04:56.250 --> 04:57.330
I have
his computer mirrored.

04:57.330 --> 04:58.960
All he ever does
is homework.

04:58.960 --> 05:01.170
So what? We just wait for him
to do something terrible,

05:01.170 --> 05:02.830
like to go the police?
He knows nothing.

05:02.830 --> 05:04.620
So you can stop freaking out
and go to class.

05:04.620 --> 05:06.380
[ Sighs ]

05:06.380 --> 05:12.540
♪♪

05:12.540 --> 05:13.620
[ Birds chirping ]

05:13.620 --> 05:14.750
There's no way
the Governor can afford

05:14.750 --> 05:16.330
to give away 64 grand.

05:16.330 --> 05:18.000
We lost our stupid prize,
not our clients.

05:18.000 --> 05:19.920
That's what matters.
Yeah, but if
this governor thing

05:19.920 --> 05:21.790
is really happening,
why haven't we started
working there yet?

05:21.790 --> 05:23.120
Because she's announcing
the project next week.

05:23.120 --> 05:24.790
-We hope.
-She signed a contract.

05:24.790 --> 05:26.500
She also signed a contract
at Caplan & Gold,

05:26.500 --> 05:28.290
whose office we are now
banned from entering.

05:28.290 --> 05:29.880
Why are you so upset?
You miss Tegan?

05:29.880 --> 05:31.210
I'm upset about prisons

05:31.210 --> 05:32.670
systematically covering up
inmate deaths

05:32.670 --> 05:34.830
by having guards lie
or hide evidence.

05:34.830 --> 05:36.670
That or make it look
like a suicide,

05:36.670 --> 05:38.250
ban families from being able
to investigate.

05:38.250 --> 05:39.710
See? At least our little
2L here gets it.

05:39.710 --> 05:40.790
Connor: I get it, too.

05:40.790 --> 05:41.830
I just think that
working with the Governor

05:41.830 --> 05:43.620
will help our clients,

05:43.620 --> 05:44.960
and that's who Annalise
cares about.
[ Cellphone chimes ]

05:44.960 --> 05:47.000
True, 'cause she definitely
does not care about us.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.290
-What does that mean?
-She just canceled class again.

05:49.290 --> 05:51.420
[ All murmuring ]

05:51.420 --> 05:56.250
♪♪

05:56.250 --> 05:58.250
Annalise.
[ Door closes ]

05:58.250 --> 06:00.750
Unfortunately,
I only have a few minutes.

06:00.750 --> 06:02.290
This will be short.

06:02.290 --> 06:05.920
I need you to push an inquest
into Nathaniel Lahey's death.

06:05.920 --> 06:08.380
My office is still
reviewing the evidence.

06:08.380 --> 06:10.620
The security cameras
at the prison were broken.

06:10.620 --> 06:12.750
If that doesn't say cover-up,
I don't know what does.

06:12.750 --> 06:15.000
Ms. Keating, this is really
not a short conversation.

06:15.000 --> 06:17.120
No. It's okay, Paige.

06:17.120 --> 06:19.000
I am so sorry

06:19.000 --> 06:20.670
that your client
went through this,

06:20.670 --> 06:22.380
but we need to focus on
launching our Project right now.

06:22.380 --> 06:24.290
The Project was about
preventing crimes

06:24.290 --> 06:26.620
against people
like Nathaniel Lahey.

06:26.620 --> 06:29.920
You think people are gonna
believe that two public servants

06:29.920 --> 06:32.460
shot an elderly man
for no reason?

06:32.460 --> 06:34.580
Not for no reason!
To hit back at me!

06:34.580 --> 06:36.380
I went before
the Supreme Court to argue

06:36.380 --> 06:38.250
that the mistreatment
of Nathaniel Lahey

06:38.250 --> 06:39.380
led him
to commit a murder.

06:39.380 --> 06:40.960
You think the guards
are happy about that?

06:40.960 --> 06:43.710
This is sounding like
a conspiracy theory.

06:43.710 --> 06:45.540
Cover-ups like this
happen all the time.

06:45.540 --> 06:48.960
And I'm protecting us,
Annalise!

06:48.960 --> 06:51.420
You, me, our Project --

06:51.420 --> 06:53.790
because that goes away
the minute the press finds out

06:53.790 --> 06:56.460
I was about to pardon
a violent man.

06:56.460 --> 06:59.000
They don't care
if he's innocent or not.

06:59.000 --> 07:01.040
They're looking
for a headline.

07:01.040 --> 07:03.380
Is that what you want?

07:03.380 --> 07:05.420
For us to hurt our chance

07:05.420 --> 07:08.790
to help millions of
wrongfully imprisoned people

07:08.790 --> 07:11.250
get out of jail?

07:11.250 --> 07:13.210
You have
to trust me here.

07:13.210 --> 07:14.540
[ Door opens ]

07:14.540 --> 07:16.000
Paige: Governor.

07:16.000 --> 07:22.960
♪♪

07:27.420 --> 07:28.420
Okay, so, let's talk
marital turkey.

07:28.420 --> 07:29.670
Why do you two
want to get married?

07:29.670 --> 07:30.830
That's pretty simple.

07:30.830 --> 07:33.080
I want to know and
spend time with Connor

07:33.080 --> 07:34.500
for the rest
of my life.

07:34.500 --> 07:36.380
Connor?

07:36.380 --> 07:37.460
What?

07:37.460 --> 07:39.290
Why do you want
to marry Oliver?

07:39.290 --> 07:41.210
Oh, uh, because
he's the best thing

07:41.210 --> 07:44.000
that's ever
happened to me.
Oh.

07:44.000 --> 07:47.250
And do either of you have any
concerns about getting married?

07:47.250 --> 07:48.790
Connor doesn't
like "Mamma Mia!"

07:48.790 --> 07:50.710
[ Laughter ]

07:50.710 --> 07:51.790
[ Sighs lightly ]

07:51.790 --> 07:53.750
Connor?

07:53.750 --> 07:55.380
No.

07:55.380 --> 07:57.120
I only say that
because, you know,

07:57.120 --> 08:00.330
it's not often that we get
young men like yourselves

08:00.330 --> 08:01.580
coming to St. Claire's.

08:02.750 --> 08:04.960
Well, I mean,
is that surprising?

08:04.960 --> 08:06.920
Historically, the church
hasn't been that cool

08:06.920 --> 08:07.880
to people like us.

08:07.880 --> 08:10.330
But we are so happy

08:10.330 --> 08:12.380
that you all
do gay marriages here.

08:12.380 --> 08:14.460
Might bring up
some issues, though.

08:14.460 --> 08:16.080
Tell me about
some of those issues.

08:16.080 --> 08:17.500
I don't think
it's really that helpful --
Well, I mean,

08:17.500 --> 08:20.880
the Presbyterian Church here
may be open-minded,

08:20.880 --> 08:23.000
but in other places,
like Ireland and Brazil,

08:23.000 --> 08:24.210
they still
won't marry gays.

08:25.040 --> 08:26.750
It's horrible.

08:26.750 --> 08:28.210
I agree.

08:28.210 --> 08:30.750
My question is,
knowing that,

08:30.750 --> 08:33.000
why did you pick St. Claire's
for your wedding?

08:33.000 --> 08:36.170
We really connect with
your philosophy on love.

08:36.170 --> 08:38.250
Not because your parents
wanted a church wedding?

08:38.250 --> 08:39.420
Connor:
His mom did.

08:41.330 --> 08:43.250
And your church
was the only one

08:43.250 --> 08:44.460
available for the day
that we wanted.

08:46.830 --> 08:50.710
Okay, Connor, I have
one more question for you --

08:50.710 --> 08:53.790
if this feels
so wrong to you,

08:53.790 --> 08:55.040
why get married here?

08:56.580 --> 08:58.380
Because
I love Oliver.

08:58.380 --> 09:04.290
♪♪

09:04.290 --> 09:06.170
I can't wait...

09:06.170 --> 09:08.620
to marry you both.

09:08.620 --> 09:09.710
[ Chuckles ]

09:09.710 --> 09:11.540
[ Chuckles ]

09:11.540 --> 09:14.540
♪♪

09:16.710 --> 09:19.420
I hope you're here
to poach me.

09:19.420 --> 09:20.920
I'm having
one of those days

09:20.920 --> 09:23.000
I want to smash all the walls
in there with a sledgehammer.

09:25.830 --> 09:27.170
The Governor
played me.

09:28.380 --> 09:30.710
How?
She had me take a job

09:30.710 --> 09:32.620
that she had no intention
of following through on.

09:32.620 --> 09:34.120
You have the proposal
in writing?

09:34.120 --> 09:35.750
She hadn't announced it
to the public yet

09:35.750 --> 09:37.790
because she never
planned to.

09:37.790 --> 09:39.420
She waited for me
to quit my job,

09:39.420 --> 09:41.420
lose my funding,
the clinic,

09:41.420 --> 09:43.040
and then she had
my client killed.

09:44.380 --> 09:46.790
Annalise...
Listen.
He was my face case.

09:46.790 --> 09:48.540
She had to destroy him
to destroy me.

09:48.540 --> 09:50.040
I got played.

09:50.040 --> 09:51.460
Okay.

09:51.460 --> 09:53.580
Did she tell you for sure
that your Project's dead?

09:53.580 --> 09:54.460
No.

09:54.460 --> 09:56.000
Then stop this.

09:56.000 --> 09:57.580
I was a fool
not to see it coming.

09:57.580 --> 09:59.120
No, you're grieving.
You're no fool.
I tried not to believe it

09:59.120 --> 10:00.540
for the past month.
Because it's not true.

10:00.540 --> 10:02.420
It is!

10:02.420 --> 10:05.330
I put a target on his back,
and she took the first shot.

10:05.330 --> 10:07.750
[ Vehicles passing in distance ]

10:12.420 --> 10:15.080
There's no way I can get
Emmett to hire you back.

10:15.080 --> 10:17.210
You know all the people
in the London office.

10:17.210 --> 10:19.790
You can find out what
the misconduct was about.

10:19.790 --> 10:21.670
So you can blackmail
your way back in here?

10:21.670 --> 10:24.290
It's for my clients.

10:24.290 --> 10:25.670
Please.

10:27.420 --> 10:29.170
♪♪

10:29.170 --> 10:30.960
I feel for you,

10:30.960 --> 10:32.540
but your mind's tired.

10:32.540 --> 10:33.960
It's making things up.

10:33.960 --> 10:35.580
-I know I'm right.
-No, you're upset

10:35.580 --> 10:37.040
and looking for
someone to blame.

10:39.330 --> 10:40.710
Get some rest.

10:40.710 --> 10:48.920
♪♪

10:48.920 --> 10:50.250
[ Car door closes ]

10:50.250 --> 10:51.710
Everyone here
has your back.

10:51.710 --> 10:53.380
So if that means
needing more time

10:53.380 --> 10:55.580
or just coming back
a few days a week at first,

10:55.580 --> 10:57.040
just ask.

10:58.620 --> 11:00.750
That's not
why I'm here.

11:00.750 --> 11:04.210
You gotta open up an inquest
on my pop's case.

11:04.210 --> 11:05.580
You're worried about
pissing people off

11:05.580 --> 11:06.750
before an election,
I know.

11:06.750 --> 11:08.670
You're my employee.

11:08.670 --> 11:11.500
Me asking for an inquest --
it's just gonna seem biased.

11:11.500 --> 11:13.210
Let a jury
hear the evidence.

11:14.750 --> 11:16.380
He stabbed
a guard, Nate.

11:16.380 --> 11:19.000
"They grabbed my gun"
is what cops say

11:19.000 --> 11:20.670
when they're
covering their ass.

11:20.670 --> 11:22.500
You claim to be on
the right side of the law?

11:22.500 --> 11:24.920
Yeah, of course I am.
Then do everything
to get the truth.

11:24.920 --> 11:26.250
Hey, calm down.
They murdered him!

11:26.250 --> 11:28.750
Made him look
like an animal!

11:28.750 --> 11:31.460
You actually have
everything in your power

11:31.460 --> 11:33.420
to do something
about it.

11:33.420 --> 11:35.080
So order
the damn inquest.

11:39.040 --> 11:41.040
Otherwise, his blood's
on your hands, too.

11:41.040 --> 11:45.330
♪♪

11:45.330 --> 11:48.170
You're gonna get slammed
by the police union,

11:48.170 --> 11:50.170
-Mayor's office...
-I know.

11:50.170 --> 11:52.250
Then let someone else
order an inquest.

11:52.250 --> 11:53.620
What's the point
of having this job

11:53.620 --> 11:55.670
if I'm afraid to actually
do this job?

11:55.670 --> 11:57.330
You're not gonna have
the job much longer

11:57.330 --> 11:59.500
if you alienate every cop
and prison guard we need

11:59.500 --> 12:02.170
to get a conviction.
Why are you
so against this?

12:02.170 --> 12:04.250
Because it's going to hurt
your career.

12:04.250 --> 12:06.500
Hm. It has nothing
to do with the fact

12:06.500 --> 12:07.880
that you're actually
pissed at Nate?
[ Elevator bell dings ]

12:07.880 --> 12:10.120
[ Elevator doors open ]

12:10.120 --> 12:13.250
Don't make me trying
to protect you a bad thing.

12:13.250 --> 12:15.920
And I'm telling you, this
isn't one of those times
where I need protecting.

12:15.920 --> 12:17.420
This is something
bigger than us.

12:17.420 --> 12:23.120
♪♪

12:23.120 --> 12:24.250
What's all this?

12:24.250 --> 12:26.040
You didn't see
Annalise's e-mail?

12:26.040 --> 12:28.670
Miller scheduled an inquest
into Nate Senior's death.

12:28.670 --> 12:29.880
She wants us
to come in tomorrow

12:29.880 --> 12:31.330
with ways she can
impact the hearing.

12:31.330 --> 12:33.380
I pulled transcripts of
old inquests from the D.A.'s.

12:34.790 --> 12:36.330
You're not in
their class, though.

12:36.330 --> 12:38.670
Yeah, but I'm, uh,
the Miller Whisperer,

12:38.670 --> 12:40.750
so if anyone knows how
to get in his head, it's me.

12:40.750 --> 12:43.750
Okay, before you all disappear
into the doom and gloom,

12:43.750 --> 12:45.790
I think we need one last
night out before the wedding.

12:45.790 --> 12:48.080
We just threw you
a bachelor party.
Yeah, the best
bachelor party ever.

12:48.080 --> 12:49.460
Our mothers were there,

12:49.460 --> 12:50.880
and Connor's
been generous enough

12:50.880 --> 12:53.000
to give Joanna
her church ceremony.

12:53.000 --> 12:55.080
So I say we shake off
the hetero

12:55.080 --> 12:56.580
and be super gay
for a night.

12:56.580 --> 12:58.880
I'm thinking Debriefed,
tequila shots,

12:58.880 --> 13:01.170
a contest to see who can
make out with the most guys --

13:01.170 --> 13:02.500
-Obviously that's me.
-Okay, thank you

13:02.500 --> 13:04.540
for giving me
what you think I want,

13:04.540 --> 13:06.880
which is not watching you
make out with other guys,

13:06.880 --> 13:08.880
but we need to work
on the Senior stuff.

13:08.880 --> 13:10.210
That's
kind of the point --

13:10.210 --> 13:13.790
to forget how depressing
the world is for one night.

13:13.790 --> 13:14.960
So, who's with me, huh?

13:14.960 --> 13:16.210
Gays gone wild!
[ Door opens ]

13:16.210 --> 13:18.210
-I'm in.
-What are you doing here?

13:18.210 --> 13:19.380
[ Door closes ]
I invited him.

13:19.380 --> 13:21.000
Are those
the excessive-force cases?

13:21.000 --> 13:22.210
Yeah.

13:23.380 --> 13:24.750
I still don't understand
how you guys

13:24.750 --> 13:27.000
ended up living next door
to each other.

13:27.000 --> 13:28.710
That I understand --
what I don't

13:28.710 --> 13:30.250
is how you became friends
with someone

13:30.250 --> 13:31.710
who took your spot
in the clinic.

13:31.710 --> 13:33.420
Well, I have
a forgiving nature.

13:33.420 --> 13:35.250
And yet, I'm still not
your plus-one to the wedding.

13:35.250 --> 13:37.420
Unless my invitation
got lost in the mail?

13:37.420 --> 13:40.120
Uh, our parents
filled up the guest list.

13:40.120 --> 13:42.500
And there's no way I'm letting
someone with those cheekbones

13:42.500 --> 13:44.120
steal all the chickadees I'll be
macking on at the wedding.

13:44.120 --> 13:45.710
Oh, charming! Okay.
[ Laughs ]

13:45.710 --> 13:48.290
Let's divide up these files
and get to work, people.

13:48.290 --> 13:50.000
[ Papers rustling ]

13:50.000 --> 13:52.250
-We have to tell Annalise.
-Not yet.

13:52.250 --> 13:54.460
He's at the house
all of the time now.

13:54.460 --> 13:55.750
Because as soon
as I shut him down,

13:55.750 --> 13:57.210
he went after Michaela.

13:57.210 --> 13:58.670
She thinks
he's a good guy.

13:58.670 --> 14:00.080
Maybe he is.

14:00.080 --> 14:02.540
Okay, well, then, tell Annalise,
let her deal with him.

14:02.540 --> 14:03.790
She's got enough
going on right now.

14:03.790 --> 14:05.580
She always
has things going on.

14:05.580 --> 14:08.000
Gabriel is Annalise's
worst nightmare.

14:08.000 --> 14:10.380
Do you understand?

14:10.380 --> 14:12.250
End of discussion.

14:12.250 --> 14:13.880
Laurel: You know
what happened last year.

14:13.880 --> 14:15.290
I almost
ruined everyone's life

14:15.290 --> 14:16.460
because I wanted to keep
everything secret.

14:16.460 --> 14:19.920
-We got through it.
-Christopher almost died!

14:19.920 --> 14:22.830
If not for Annalise,
I would not have him.

14:22.830 --> 14:24.620
Please, just tell her.

14:24.620 --> 14:26.080
♪♪

14:31.250 --> 14:32.830
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

14:32.830 --> 14:35.290
Ryan:
Harry told me you made a mess
on the 9th hole at Birkdale.

14:35.290 --> 14:37.670
[ Chuckles ] That's why
he can't hold down a wife.

14:37.670 --> 14:39.330
Can't stop lying.

14:39.330 --> 14:41.120
I'll be in touch.

14:41.120 --> 14:44.290
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:44.290 --> 14:46.290
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

14:46.290 --> 14:48.330
[ Conversations continue ]

14:50.960 --> 14:53.210
Were you just interviewing
Ryan Stack?

14:53.210 --> 14:54.540
You two
know each other?

14:54.540 --> 14:55.880
He was an associate
for Unger and Pace

14:55.880 --> 14:57.460
when I was an intern.

14:57.460 --> 14:59.620
Oh. You think he'd make
a good addition here?

14:59.620 --> 15:01.040
Hell, no.

15:01.040 --> 15:03.580
He's conniving,
arrogant, manipulative...

15:03.580 --> 15:04.710
Great.

15:04.710 --> 15:06.500
We need a shark
to replace you-know-who.

15:06.500 --> 15:07.960
Why replace
Annalise at all?

15:07.960 --> 15:09.460
We need
new business.

15:09.460 --> 15:11.250
I've brought in three accounts
in the last month.

15:11.250 --> 15:13.170
Tegan, no one's denying
what you do for the firm.

15:13.170 --> 15:15.170
Then give me
the responsibility and pay

15:15.170 --> 15:16.460
you plan on giving
to that blowhard.

15:16.460 --> 15:17.710
Aren't you
forgetting something?

15:20.670 --> 15:24.290
The FBI was responsible
for killing Antares, not me.

15:24.290 --> 15:26.000
Well...
[inhales sharply]

15:26.000 --> 15:29.040
...that's not
how the board sees it.

15:29.040 --> 15:30.960
I can't be the sole partner
taking the fall

15:30.960 --> 15:33.120
for an account that
was rotten to begin with.

15:33.120 --> 15:34.580
That's funny.

15:34.580 --> 15:36.540
No, that's exactly
what I told the board

15:36.540 --> 15:37.750
when they transferred me
from London.

15:39.460 --> 15:41.330
Don't like eating crow
for the firm?

15:41.330 --> 15:42.540
Maybe this isn't
the right job for you.

15:42.540 --> 15:49.750
♪♪

15:49.750 --> 15:51.790
Let's go.

15:51.790 --> 15:54.830
We all know that investigations
into police officers

15:54.830 --> 15:56.330
who've killed
people of color

15:56.330 --> 15:58.420
rarely favor the victim.

15:58.420 --> 16:01.540
So hit me up with ways that
we can make this go our way.

16:02.790 --> 16:04.710
Ms. Castillo.

16:04.710 --> 16:06.170
In an inquest,
the judge can choose

16:06.170 --> 16:07.620
who questions
the witnesses,

16:07.620 --> 16:09.620
so I say we convince
Judge Cruz to let you do it.

16:09.620 --> 16:10.830
That's a great idea.

16:10.830 --> 16:13.210
So great that I tried it
first thing this morning.

16:13.210 --> 16:15.540
I was Nathaniel Lahey's
lawyer through two trials.

16:15.540 --> 16:18.210
It's within your power to let me
question those guards.

16:18.210 --> 16:20.750
D.A. Miller's more than capable
of handling this inquest.

16:20.750 --> 16:22.790
I'm the only one who's lived
and breathed this case.

16:22.790 --> 16:24.710
Exactly.
You're too close.

16:24.710 --> 16:26.790
D.A. Miller is objective,
and, therefore,

16:26.790 --> 16:29.670
the only person questioning
witnesses in my courtroom.

16:29.670 --> 16:31.620
[ Door creaks ]

16:32.670 --> 16:34.750
Inquest juries are made up
of only six people.

16:34.750 --> 16:36.500
There's no voir dire --
they're randomly selected

16:36.500 --> 16:37.670
from the county's
jury pool.

16:37.670 --> 16:39.380
I suggest we try
finding out their names.

16:39.380 --> 16:40.880
That's
jury tampering.

16:40.880 --> 16:42.670
You want me
to get disbarred?

16:42.670 --> 16:44.290
I wasn't suggesting
that you do it.

16:46.710 --> 16:49.170
My password isn't giving me
access to the juror's office.

16:49.170 --> 16:51.380
-Try Miller's.
-I don't have his.

16:51.380 --> 16:53.170
Wait, I have Bonnie's.

16:53.170 --> 16:55.540
I just changed
all my passwords.

16:55.540 --> 16:56.880
And how stupid are you?

16:56.880 --> 16:58.620
This case is under
a magnifying glass.
Oh.

16:58.620 --> 17:00.120
It's for Nate.

17:00.120 --> 17:01.580
You mean Annalise.

17:01.580 --> 17:03.960
So she can help Nate.
What's the difference?

17:03.960 --> 17:05.080
You tell her,
if she wants my help,

17:05.080 --> 17:06.540
she should
return my calls.

17:06.540 --> 17:10.540
♪♪

17:10.540 --> 17:11.920
Michaela: One of
the advantages of an inquest

17:11.920 --> 17:13.670
is that hearsay is allowed --
we can exploit that

17:13.670 --> 17:15.880
and have Miller introduce
uncorroborated evidence.

17:15.880 --> 17:18.880
What evidence?
The corrections officers'
bad character.

17:18.880 --> 17:20.960
Their employment record
is squeaky clean.

17:20.960 --> 17:23.250
Right. But what about
their personal lives?

17:23.250 --> 17:24.750
Statistics show that
correction officers

17:24.750 --> 17:27.210
commit domestic abuse at least
twice the national average.

17:27.210 --> 17:29.460
What he said.

17:29.460 --> 17:31.170
Find something.
Make me a believer.

17:31.170 --> 17:35.080
♪♪

17:35.080 --> 17:36.330
Oliver:
This guard is an angel.

17:36.330 --> 17:38.170
He shot Nate Senior
in the head.

17:38.170 --> 17:40.290
But he also sings
in his church choir.
Then hack
the other guard.

17:40.290 --> 17:41.960
She probably stabbed
herself in the leg.

17:41.960 --> 17:43.040
Who knows what else
she's capable of?

17:43.040 --> 17:45.830
What's her name?
Paula Gladden.

17:45.830 --> 17:48.290
Annalise: Paula Gladden
beats her husband.

17:48.290 --> 17:49.830
He never reported it
to the police,

17:49.830 --> 17:52.460
but he had multiple trips
to the E.R. for beatings

17:52.460 --> 17:55.750
that medical records list
as "domestic disputes."

17:55.750 --> 17:57.710
How'd you get this?
Well, if I tell you,

17:57.710 --> 17:59.120
you'd never
be able to use it.

18:00.250 --> 18:02.120
That's exactly
why I can't use it.

18:02.120 --> 18:04.380
Oh, no,
you're gonna use it...

18:04.380 --> 18:06.330
but not before
you get her to testify

18:06.330 --> 18:08.250
that she never
abused her husband.

18:08.250 --> 18:10.290
It'll prove that
she's a violent liar,

18:10.290 --> 18:11.880
and that's more than enough
to convince a jury

18:11.880 --> 18:13.080
that this was a cover-up.

18:14.830 --> 18:16.120
You got this.

18:16.120 --> 18:18.750
♪♪

18:18.750 --> 18:21.250
The inmate was getting
increasingly agitated,

18:21.250 --> 18:23.290
so I approached
to calm him.

18:23.290 --> 18:24.750
That's when he jammed
the pencil into my leg

18:24.750 --> 18:26.620
and reached for my gun.

18:26.620 --> 18:27.670
He would've
gotten it, too,

18:27.670 --> 18:29.170
if C.O. Wagner
hadn't followed protocol

18:29.170 --> 18:31.250
and saved my life.
[ Door opens ]

18:31.250 --> 18:32.710
That must have been
a relief to your husband

18:32.710 --> 18:34.120
that you made it home
that night.
[ Door closes ]

18:34.120 --> 18:36.040
It was.

18:36.040 --> 18:38.330
But he knows
what comes with the job.

18:38.330 --> 18:39.750
Does a violent streak
come with the job?

18:41.420 --> 18:43.790
Sorry?
Have you ever been abusive
to your husband?

18:43.790 --> 18:45.210
No. What are you
talking about?

18:46.420 --> 18:48.250
This photo is
what I'm talking about.

18:50.330 --> 18:51.960
Judge Cruz: Where'd you obtain
this evidence, Mr. Miller?

18:51.960 --> 18:54.960
An anonymous messenger sent
these to my office this morning.

18:54.960 --> 18:57.040
I had nothing to do
with his injuries.

18:57.040 --> 18:59.500
Really? 'Cause
hospital records noted

18:59.500 --> 19:01.540
that the injuries were the
result of a domestic dispute.

19:01.540 --> 19:03.710
A domestic dispute between
my brother and husband.

19:03.710 --> 19:05.380
They were drinking,

19:05.380 --> 19:07.080
being stupid --
They why did the nurse

19:07.080 --> 19:08.420
write that the cuts
on your husband's face

19:08.420 --> 19:10.080
were caused by a ring?

19:10.080 --> 19:11.540
Isn't the real explanation
that they were caused

19:11.540 --> 19:13.670
by the engagement ring
on your finger?

19:13.670 --> 19:15.500
That's enough,
Mr. Miller.
Your Honor,
this speaks directly

19:15.500 --> 19:17.620
to the credibility
of one of the only people

19:17.620 --> 19:19.420
who claimed that Mr. Lahey
was violent that night.

19:19.420 --> 19:21.330
Only if you have proof
Mrs. Gladden

19:21.330 --> 19:23.170
was responsible
for her husband's injuries --

19:23.170 --> 19:24.580
otherwise,
this line of questioning

19:24.580 --> 19:27.210
is out of the scope
of this hearing.

19:27.210 --> 19:28.210
Move on.

19:29.830 --> 19:31.330
We need
a new strategy.

19:31.330 --> 19:33.500
You know
I don't work for you.

19:33.500 --> 19:35.790
Put me on the stand.
[ Door closes ]

19:35.790 --> 19:37.080
As his past lawyer,

19:37.080 --> 19:38.620
I could speak to
Nate Senior's state of mind.

19:38.620 --> 19:40.040
The jury will see you
as biased.

19:40.040 --> 19:41.420
You were
too intimate with him.

19:41.420 --> 19:43.790
The intimacy is what
makes me an authority.

19:43.790 --> 19:45.710
Look.
You're a great lawyer.

19:45.710 --> 19:47.420
But you don't keep
Michael Jordan on the bench

19:47.420 --> 19:48.830
when the game
is on the line.

19:48.830 --> 19:50.460
Okay, that line might work
with your students,

19:50.460 --> 19:51.710
but I'm the freaking D.A.

19:51.710 --> 19:53.040
Stand down.

19:53.040 --> 19:54.670
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:58.250 --> 20:00.330
-Can we talk?
-I'm late for the Governor.

20:00.330 --> 20:02.580
[ Conversations continue ]

20:02.580 --> 20:04.210
[ Birds chirping ]

20:04.210 --> 20:06.380
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

20:06.380 --> 20:10.040
Annalise, I am so sorry
to call you in last minute.

20:10.040 --> 20:11.670
Paige said
it was important.

20:11.670 --> 20:14.750
I'm just gonna
pull the Band-Aid off here.

20:16.500 --> 20:19.920
Due to the negative press
around Mr. Lahey's death

20:19.920 --> 20:21.380
and reports
that the inquest

20:21.380 --> 20:24.210
is going as poorly
as I feared,

20:24.210 --> 20:25.710
we won't be able
to move forward

20:25.710 --> 20:28.580
with the
Fair Defense Project.

20:28.580 --> 20:30.710
Why?
Like I said,

20:30.710 --> 20:33.790
now that this inquest is proving
Mr. Lahey was violent --

20:33.790 --> 20:36.250
No, I mean
the real reason.

20:36.250 --> 20:38.540
Annalise,
you have to understand

20:38.540 --> 20:41.580
this is as painful for me
as it is for you.

20:41.580 --> 20:43.500
Please.
We are still gonna do

20:43.500 --> 20:44.880
whatever we can
to support you --

20:44.880 --> 20:47.420
I can't wait
to take you down.

20:47.420 --> 20:49.080
Paige: Okay,
this meeting is over.

20:49.080 --> 20:50.830
Then call
your damn guards!

20:54.170 --> 20:56.080
Just like you called
the prison guards that night?

20:56.080 --> 20:57.540
Ordered them to do
your dirty work?

20:57.540 --> 20:58.960
Okay, I'm getting security
on the phone right now.

20:58.960 --> 21:00.170
You sure
you want to do that?

21:00.170 --> 21:01.750
Because I can go
on live TV right now

21:01.750 --> 21:04.120
and say that your boss
ordered a kill on my client.

21:04.120 --> 21:06.040
You are deeply mistaken,
Annalise.

21:06.040 --> 21:08.540
And you're basic.

21:08.540 --> 21:11.000
You knew how easy it would be to
paint the black man as a threat

21:11.000 --> 21:12.670
to that white woman.

21:12.670 --> 21:13.830
It's a story your people
have been telling

21:13.830 --> 21:15.120
since the dawn of time.

21:15.120 --> 21:17.000
Do you understand
how unstable you sound?

21:17.000 --> 21:19.670
But this time,
you used it against me.

21:19.670 --> 21:22.250
Anything to take down the enemy
you knew was smarter than you.

21:24.500 --> 21:26.880
You're not smarter than me,
Annalise.

21:26.880 --> 21:29.710
Otherwise,
you'd know I have this.

21:29.710 --> 21:30.920
[ Folder thumps lightly ]

21:30.920 --> 21:32.420
We do thorough
background checks

21:32.420 --> 21:34.460
on anyone
coming to work for us.

21:34.460 --> 21:35.790
Like I have
anything else to hide.

21:35.790 --> 21:37.580
That's what I thought,

21:37.580 --> 21:40.290
but then we uncovered
your adoption paperwork.

21:42.540 --> 21:44.620
You just got your reputation
back, Annalise.

21:44.620 --> 21:46.750
Don't make us
destroy it again.

21:48.290 --> 21:50.170
Bring it.

21:50.170 --> 21:51.500
You think
I'm scared of this?

21:51.500 --> 21:54.040
You've never gone up against
a Governor before, have you?

21:54.040 --> 21:56.290
And you've never been up
against me, either.

21:56.290 --> 21:58.580
Try it. Pick this fight.
[ Door opens ]

21:58.580 --> 22:01.210
His name is Nathaniel Lahey,
and I'll take a thousand bullets

22:01.210 --> 22:03.040
to make you pay
for what you did to him.

22:03.040 --> 22:05.080
♪♪

22:10.210 --> 22:11.210
How'd it go
with the Governor?

22:11.210 --> 22:12.250
I'm too tired
to talk about it.

22:14.210 --> 22:15.540
You want soda?

22:18.040 --> 22:19.830
What's wrong?

22:19.830 --> 22:22.210
Ron has a friend who works
at the Governor's office.

22:22.210 --> 22:24.380
[ Refrigerator door closes ]
She pulled the offer?

22:24.380 --> 22:25.710
[ Sighs ]

22:25.710 --> 22:27.790
You know, for something
that's supposed to be a secret,

22:27.790 --> 22:29.750
everyone in town
seems to know about it.

22:32.880 --> 22:34.210
I'm worried about you.

22:36.290 --> 22:38.330
You're worried
I'm pissed at you.

22:38.330 --> 22:40.750
So you didn't listen
to me about Julie -- so what?

22:40.750 --> 22:43.210
I'm over it.

22:43.210 --> 22:45.580
I'm worried
you're drinking again.

22:45.580 --> 22:47.960
[ Sighs ]

22:47.960 --> 22:49.540
You know what?

22:49.540 --> 22:50.920
Leave.

22:50.920 --> 22:53.120
Because you are?
No.

22:53.120 --> 22:54.710
You're not allowed
to ask me that anymore.

22:54.710 --> 22:56.000
I'll throw
your ass out.

22:58.250 --> 22:59.960
[ Clattering ]
You know what?

22:59.960 --> 23:02.170
How about I just throw you
off my deck out there?

23:02.170 --> 23:03.670
You think I won't? Hm?

23:05.460 --> 23:07.540
I'd tell you if I was
drinking again, Bonnie.

23:07.540 --> 23:16.620
♪♪

23:16.620 --> 23:25.620
♪♪

23:25.620 --> 23:34.620
♪♪

23:34.620 --> 23:36.170
[ Bottle thumps ]

23:36.170 --> 23:39.500
♪♪

23:39.500 --> 23:41.040
You were good
for so long.

23:41.040 --> 23:42.620
You can
get there again.

23:45.500 --> 23:47.920
The Governor knows
about the adoption.

23:47.920 --> 23:54.540
♪♪

23:54.540 --> 24:01.000
♪♪

24:01.000 --> 24:03.460
[ Glass taps ]

24:03.460 --> 24:11.500
♪♪

24:11.500 --> 24:13.880
[ Sighs ]

24:13.880 --> 24:15.380
One more won't hurt.

24:15.380 --> 24:23.830
♪♪

24:23.830 --> 24:28.290
♪♪

24:28.290 --> 24:29.790
[ Glass taps ]

24:29.790 --> 24:32.500
♪♪

24:32.500 --> 24:40.960
♪♪

24:40.960 --> 24:49.620
♪♪

24:49.620 --> 24:58.080
♪♪

24:58.080 --> 24:59.170
[ Beeps ]

25:01.670 --> 25:03.880
[ Cellphone rings ]

25:03.880 --> 25:05.580
Hey.
What's going on?

25:05.580 --> 25:07.460
Uh, I'm calling Annalise.
Is she there?

25:07.460 --> 25:09.880
She's asleep.
I just put her to bed.

25:09.880 --> 25:11.460
What the hell?
Is she okay?

25:11.460 --> 25:13.250
She's drinking again.

25:13.250 --> 25:19.830
♪♪

25:19.830 --> 25:27.750
♪♪

25:27.750 --> 25:29.420
Bonnie?

25:29.420 --> 25:31.040
[ Birds chirping ]

25:31.040 --> 25:33.080
[ Horn honking in distance ]

25:35.170 --> 25:37.170
[ Cellphone ringing, vibrating ]

25:40.290 --> 25:41.580
[ Cellphone beeps ]

25:42.880 --> 25:44.380
Hello?

25:44.380 --> 25:47.120
I stayed up all night trying
to think of a way

25:47.120 --> 25:50.500
to ensure we win this.

25:50.500 --> 25:53.500
But I came up
with nothing.

25:53.500 --> 25:55.380
So, how about we go
with your idea

25:55.380 --> 25:56.500
and put you on the stand?

25:56.500 --> 25:57.500
You sure?

25:58.500 --> 26:01.210
100%.

26:01.210 --> 26:02.620
Let's win this.

26:02.620 --> 26:04.710
♪♪

26:04.710 --> 26:06.290
Miller: Ms. Keating,

26:06.290 --> 26:08.250
during the Medical Examiner's
press conference,

26:08.250 --> 26:10.330
she suggested that
your client, Mr. Lahey,

26:10.330 --> 26:13.330
was not taking
his anti-psychotic medication.

26:13.330 --> 26:14.880
Do you find that
suggestion credible?

26:14.880 --> 26:17.210
-Not at all.
-Mm.

26:17.210 --> 26:19.290
But the tests
performed on Mr. Lahey

26:19.290 --> 26:21.170
showed no signs of
these drugs in his system.

26:21.170 --> 26:23.710
Well, I'd like to talk to
the person who ran those tests

26:23.710 --> 26:25.330
to see if they
were encouraged

26:25.330 --> 26:26.580
to say
whatever they needed

26:26.580 --> 26:28.120
in order to make
that story stick.

26:28.120 --> 26:29.580
What story
are you referring to?

26:29.580 --> 26:32.330
That Mr. Lahey was violent
with the guards that night.

26:32.330 --> 26:33.750
You believe they're
trying to cover up

26:33.750 --> 26:35.080
some sort of misconduct?

26:35.080 --> 26:37.330
No, I don't believe it --
I know it.

26:37.330 --> 26:40.080
Not once did Mr. Lahey
act violently in my presence.

26:40.080 --> 26:41.960
My notes of my visits with him
will prove this.

26:41.960 --> 26:43.460
You can read them
yourselves.

26:43.460 --> 26:45.000
Judge Cruz: Do not address
the jury, Ms. Keating.

26:47.120 --> 26:50.710
This is a man who sat
in the Supreme Court

26:50.710 --> 26:53.500
and listened to the most
powerful judges in the world

26:53.500 --> 26:55.250
call him a monster,

26:55.250 --> 26:56.960
and not once
did he make a sound.

26:56.960 --> 26:58.580
That's how together
he was.

26:58.580 --> 27:01.120
So to believe that he suddenly
picked a fight with guards

27:01.120 --> 27:03.920
on the last night that he knew
he'd ever have to see them,

27:03.920 --> 27:05.460
how does that
make sense?

27:05.460 --> 27:07.920
Well, he was a violent criminal
in his past.

27:07.920 --> 27:09.500
Who's to say he couldn't
be violent again?

27:09.500 --> 27:11.830
He was violent only
one time in his life,

27:11.830 --> 27:15.330
and that was during
a severe mental-health episode.

27:15.330 --> 27:17.210
What those guards are hoping
that you believe

27:17.210 --> 27:19.710
is the oldest, most racist
stories in our country.

27:19.710 --> 27:21.830
-I said no addressing the jury.
-Emmett Till,

27:21.830 --> 27:24.670
Scottsboro Boys,
Central Park Five...

27:24.670 --> 27:26.250
[ Gavel bangs ]
Judge Cruz:
Ms. Keating!

27:26.250 --> 27:30.540
These false accusations all
started with the same lie --

27:30.540 --> 27:34.330
that black men are wired
to attack white women.

27:34.330 --> 27:37.290
It's a stereotype sewn so deep
in the fabric of this country

27:37.290 --> 27:38.710
that they just know
that you're gonna ignore

27:38.710 --> 27:40.500
huge plot holes
in their cover-up --

27:40.500 --> 27:42.750
that the surveillance cameras
were broken,

27:42.750 --> 27:45.210
or that an elderly man
could physically overpower

27:45.210 --> 27:47.040
two 30-something
guards --

27:47.040 --> 27:49.380
when there's only
one true story here,

27:49.380 --> 27:51.880
that those two people
right there

27:51.880 --> 27:54.210
wanted to punish
my client

27:54.210 --> 27:56.830
for exposing the torture and
abuse happening in our prisons.

27:56.830 --> 27:58.380
Do not address anyone
in this courtroom.
So they slaughtered him.

27:58.380 --> 28:00.580
They shot a defenseless man
in the head,

28:00.580 --> 28:02.170
and here we are...
[ Gavel banging ]

28:02.170 --> 28:04.380
...another black man's body
being paraded in the court

28:04.380 --> 28:06.040
and me having to beg
for justice...
Ms. Keating,
may I remind you

28:06.040 --> 28:08.040
that you are a witness here?
...beg for you to see him
as a human being.

28:08.040 --> 28:09.170
I will not stand
for this grandstanding...
Six people...

28:09.170 --> 28:11.210
...in my courtroom.
...and you're the only ones
who have the power to do right.

28:11.210 --> 28:12.710
So do right!
[ Gavel banging ]

28:12.710 --> 28:14.170
Judge Cruz: Ms. Keating!

28:14.170 --> 28:15.710
You are dismissed
from the stand.

28:15.710 --> 28:18.420
The jury will hear
no further testimony from you.

28:18.420 --> 28:20.250
Mr. Miller,
no further questions.

28:20.250 --> 28:23.000
Your witness has disregarded
my warnings for the last time.

28:23.000 --> 28:24.460
She may step down.

28:24.460 --> 28:25.790
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:25.790 --> 28:27.830
Asher.
How'd it go?

28:27.830 --> 28:29.210
How do you think?
AK killed it.

28:33.210 --> 28:34.580
I-I like him
for you.

28:35.670 --> 28:37.080
Miller.

28:37.080 --> 28:41.040
I know I'm not supposed
to know, but, uh...

28:41.040 --> 28:44.170
he was this big-mopey-beard-face
when you were out sick,

28:44.170 --> 28:47.040
and, um, it was
kind of adorable.

28:47.040 --> 28:49.170
No one else
here knows, Asher.

28:49.170 --> 28:50.540
Yeah, and I won't
say anything.

28:50.540 --> 28:52.380
I...

28:52.380 --> 28:54.000
I'm happy for you.

28:57.620 --> 29:06.750
♪♪

29:06.750 --> 29:08.790
I understand the jury
has reached a verdict.

29:08.790 --> 29:10.120
Yes, Your Honor.

29:10.120 --> 29:13.420
♪♪

29:13.420 --> 29:16.710
In the matter of
Nathaniel Lahey Senior's death,

29:16.710 --> 29:19.460
we, the jury, find
no evidence of criminal acts

29:19.460 --> 29:22.500
or negligence
by anyone involved.

29:22.500 --> 29:24.040
Accordingly, we concur

29:24.040 --> 29:25.790
with the Medical Examiner's
conclusion

29:25.790 --> 29:27.920
that the homicide
was justifiable

29:27.920 --> 29:29.750
and that no charges
be filed with the matter.

29:29.750 --> 29:31.460
Thank you.

29:31.460 --> 29:34.420
This inquest is closed.
Jury discharged.

29:34.420 --> 29:35.750
[ Gavel bangs ]

29:35.750 --> 29:37.500
[ Audience murmuring ]

29:37.500 --> 29:45.000
♪♪

29:45.000 --> 29:52.080
♪♪

29:57.000 --> 30:00.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

30:00.210 --> 30:01.000
Hey.

30:03.290 --> 30:05.210
I can leave
if you'd rather be alone.

30:06.540 --> 30:09.080
[ Doors opening, closing
in distance ]

30:09.080 --> 30:11.710
[ Indistinct conversations ]

30:15.920 --> 30:17.000
[ Conversations continue ]

30:20.750 --> 30:23.250
He deserved
so much better.

30:23.250 --> 30:25.460
I know
that's not enough,

30:25.460 --> 30:26.920
especially with how
you've always protected us

30:26.920 --> 30:30.080
from God knows what,

30:30.080 --> 30:32.830
but if there's
anything I can do...

30:32.830 --> 30:35.960
yell at someone
or organize a protest

30:35.960 --> 30:38.670
or just...

30:38.670 --> 30:40.170
be angry for you...

30:42.620 --> 30:45.000
...please tell me.

30:45.000 --> 30:46.830
[ Conversations continue ]

30:55.460 --> 30:57.120
Thanks.

30:57.120 --> 31:04.250
♪♪

31:05.580 --> 31:07.250
I talked to my people
in London.

31:07.250 --> 31:08.290
[ Door closes ]

31:08.290 --> 31:09.830
They were all
tight-lipped.

31:09.830 --> 31:13.210
So I called my IT guy,
and he found this.

31:13.210 --> 31:15.880
Our boss's misconduct is a lot
more messy than we thought.

31:17.710 --> 31:19.290
You don't want to know
what changed my mind?

31:19.290 --> 31:21.080
I figured
you just liked me.

31:21.080 --> 31:22.750
If you're right
about the Governor --

31:22.750 --> 31:26.500
and something in my gut
tells me you are --

31:26.500 --> 31:28.540
I can't wake up
to any more headlines

31:28.540 --> 31:31.880
about innocent, unarmed
black men getting shot.

31:31.880 --> 31:34.540
And our Governor needs to be the
first one we burn at the stake.

31:34.540 --> 31:36.120
But so you know,

31:36.120 --> 31:37.880
you're gonna
owe me someday.

31:37.880 --> 31:39.250
I'm good for it.

31:39.250 --> 31:45.960
♪♪

31:45.960 --> 31:48.250
[ Dance music plays ]

31:48.250 --> 31:50.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:50.170 --> 31:52.500
♪♪

31:52.500 --> 31:53.830
Here we go!

31:53.830 --> 31:55.960
Tequila shots, shots!

31:55.960 --> 31:57.500
Did you order them
with poison?

31:57.500 --> 31:59.420
Because dying sounds
really nice right now.

31:59.420 --> 32:01.920
You can die after the wedding
so that Connor's dad

32:01.920 --> 32:04.000
doesn't get mad
that we wasted an invite.

32:04.000 --> 32:05.790
Now, I say
we do another round,

32:05.790 --> 32:08.460
and then
the contest begins.

32:08.460 --> 32:10.170
I'm not letting you make out
with dudes, Oli.

32:10.170 --> 32:13.290
No. Oliver's right.

32:13.290 --> 32:17.210
Is this country a scary,
evil, racist place? Yes.

32:17.210 --> 32:19.040
Are those guards probably home
with their families right now,

32:19.040 --> 32:20.790
not giving a damn
about what they did --

32:20.790 --> 32:24.460
You're not making
anyone feel better.
You two are in love.

32:24.460 --> 32:28.250
That's a glorious thing,
so we need to embrace that.

32:28.250 --> 32:29.920
Otherwise,
the terrorists win,

32:29.920 --> 32:32.170
and they cannot win.

32:32.170 --> 32:34.790
Hell, no, because we are
going to work for Annalise

32:34.790 --> 32:37.620
at the Governor's office --
-No, you're not.

32:37.620 --> 32:39.790
Okay, that is not the can-do
attitude we need right now.

32:39.790 --> 32:40.960
No, Miller said that

32:40.960 --> 32:42.080
the Governor pulled the plug
on the program.

32:42.080 --> 32:43.670
Didn't AK tell you?

32:43.670 --> 32:44.620
Now can we die?

32:44.620 --> 32:46.580
♪♪

32:46.580 --> 32:48.040
No. No!

32:48.040 --> 32:50.290
We have survived so much,
all of us.

32:50.290 --> 32:52.920
So pick up your damn
shot glasses.

32:52.920 --> 32:55.420
-Right now.
-[ Sighs ]

32:55.420 --> 32:57.920
To Nate Senior
and the hope

32:57.920 --> 33:00.920
that, someday,
we will live in a world

33:00.920 --> 33:03.960
that isn't always so terrible
all the time.

33:03.960 --> 33:05.500
[ Glasses clinking ]

33:05.500 --> 33:08.710
♪♪

33:12.580 --> 33:14.250
Ms. Keating,
you can't be here.

33:16.380 --> 33:17.500
Do you want me
to call security?

33:17.500 --> 33:18.460
Not yet.

33:19.920 --> 33:21.710
I'm -- I'm a good guy,
Annalise,

33:21.710 --> 33:23.380
but not so good that
there's any chance in hell

33:23.380 --> 33:25.170
I'm hiring you back.

33:25.170 --> 33:26.620
I know
about your misconduct.
[ Folder thumps lightly ]

33:31.380 --> 33:33.120
[ Papers rustle ]

33:33.120 --> 33:35.080
So what?
This is blackmail?

33:35.080 --> 33:36.540
It was going to be.
Get out of here.

33:36.540 --> 33:38.000
I can fix this
for you.

33:40.460 --> 33:41.920
You're not the one to blame
for what happened.

33:41.920 --> 33:43.460
It was her --

33:43.460 --> 33:45.080
a woman you said you loved
who betrayed you,

33:45.080 --> 33:46.710
and I know
how that feels,

33:46.710 --> 33:48.330
to trust someone you love
with your life,

33:48.330 --> 33:49.420
only to have them
stab you in the back.

33:49.420 --> 33:50.920
Oh, you mean
like you did to me?

33:50.920 --> 33:53.620
I mean my husband.

33:53.620 --> 33:55.460
He played the good boy
for 20 years.

33:55.460 --> 33:58.330
That's how long
I fell for his act.

33:58.330 --> 34:00.330
I promised myself I'd never
get played like that again,

34:00.330 --> 34:03.210
and here comes
the Governor.

34:03.210 --> 34:05.540
-I feel like a damn fool.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

34:05.540 --> 34:07.210
You know, you always know the
right thing to say, Annalise.

34:07.210 --> 34:09.920
-It's not a ploy.
-Everything with you is.

34:09.920 --> 34:11.120
I'm desperate, Emmett.

34:13.750 --> 34:15.620
I'll do whatever I can
to fix this for you.

34:17.040 --> 34:19.750
How?
I'll figure it out.

34:19.750 --> 34:22.620
But this -- playing the good
little boy for this firm --

34:22.620 --> 34:25.580
ohh, I can fight this
for you.

34:25.580 --> 34:29.380
♪♪

34:29.380 --> 34:30.750
Take me back.

34:30.750 --> 34:35.170
♪♪

34:35.170 --> 34:36.580
[ Dance music plays ]
Connor: How do you do that?

34:36.580 --> 34:39.290
-Do what?
-Know exactly what I need.

34:39.290 --> 34:42.920
Oh, who doesn't always
need go-go boys and tequila?

34:42.920 --> 34:44.920
[ Laughs ] I meant a night out
without our moms.

34:44.920 --> 34:47.380
Or in a church.
Hey, listen.

34:48.710 --> 34:51.380
I will marry you in a church
a million times,

34:51.380 --> 34:53.620
as long as I get
to be with you.

34:53.620 --> 34:54.710
You should
write that down.

34:54.710 --> 34:56.710
That would be good
for the vows.

34:56.710 --> 34:58.500
[ Chuckles ]

34:58.500 --> 34:59.710
[ Insects chirping ]

34:59.710 --> 35:01.170
[ Music continues ]

35:01.170 --> 35:08.960
♪♪

35:08.960 --> 35:10.540
Ugh, get a room,
faggots.

35:12.040 --> 35:13.580
Hey, what did you say?
Hey, just ignore him.

35:13.580 --> 35:15.620
Hey, douchebag. Why don't you
say that to our face?

35:15.620 --> 35:17.420
Or we could just go home
and eat ice cream.

35:17.420 --> 35:19.250
You didn't hear me
the first time?
No, no, no, no.

35:19.250 --> 35:20.580
I want you
to say it again.

35:20.580 --> 35:22.620
Connor, please.
Come on. I dare you.

35:22.620 --> 35:23.830
I said,
get a room, fa--

35:23.830 --> 35:25.540
[ Grunts ]
Oh, my God!

35:25.540 --> 35:27.080
Ohh.

35:27.080 --> 35:28.540
Come on.
Let's go.

35:30.170 --> 35:32.120
-[ Grunts ]
-Oh, my God!

35:32.120 --> 35:34.620
Stop! Stop!
Get off of him!

35:34.620 --> 35:36.460
-[ Grunts ]
-Somebody, help!

35:36.460 --> 35:37.830
Hey! You guys!

35:37.830 --> 35:38.880
[ Both grunting ]

35:38.880 --> 35:40.330
[ Man shouting ]

35:40.330 --> 35:41.670
Stop, please! Help!

35:41.670 --> 35:43.210
Ohh!

35:43.210 --> 35:44.290
-Connor, please!
-[ Grunting ]

35:44.290 --> 35:46.000
Please, stop!

35:46.000 --> 35:47.290
Stop, please! Help!
Connor!
[ Groaning ]

35:52.170 --> 35:53.540
We said gays gone wild,
right?

35:53.540 --> 35:55.210
Yup.

35:55.210 --> 35:56.710
[ Sighs ]

35:56.710 --> 35:58.080
Did I freak you out?

36:00.000 --> 36:01.830
No.

36:01.830 --> 36:04.250
Look, just tell your mother
that I...

36:04.250 --> 36:05.620
fell off a scooter
or something.

36:05.620 --> 36:08.380
Hey. [ Sighs ]

36:08.380 --> 36:10.920
It's not your fault
the world's so awful right now.

36:10.920 --> 36:13.040
It's his.

36:13.040 --> 36:16.290
'Cause if we saw him
on the street like that --

36:16.290 --> 36:20.290
being himself, happy --

36:20.290 --> 36:23.420
and we would have smiled
and kept on walking.

36:23.420 --> 36:25.960
♪♪

36:25.960 --> 36:27.670
He's just lucky
my big muscles were there

36:27.670 --> 36:28.790
to stop you
from killing him.

36:28.790 --> 36:30.040
[ Both chuckle ]

36:30.040 --> 36:31.170
No making me laugh.

36:31.170 --> 36:32.500
I'm sorry.

36:32.500 --> 36:35.960
♪♪

36:35.960 --> 36:37.830
Don't leave me.

36:37.830 --> 36:39.380
I have to go.

36:39.380 --> 36:40.790
Please,
just one more minute.

36:40.790 --> 36:42.620
I've missed our snuggles.

36:42.620 --> 36:44.790
You're gonna be mortified
you said this in the morning.

36:44.790 --> 36:47.210
30 seconds, then.

36:47.210 --> 36:49.250
-Asher.
-10 seconds?

36:49.250 --> 36:51.000
-Fine.
-Yay.

36:51.000 --> 36:54.210
Just count slow.

36:54.210 --> 36:56.620
10, 9...

36:56.620 --> 36:59.000
Slower.

36:59.000 --> 37:02.920
[ Whispering ]
7...6...

37:02.920 --> 37:05.250
[ Sighs ]

37:05.250 --> 37:07.210
...5...

37:26.000 --> 37:27.380
[ Knocking on door ]

37:30.830 --> 37:32.120
Hey.

37:32.120 --> 37:33.670
I just put
a very, uh...

37:35.000 --> 37:37.170
...drunk Asher to bed,
so, um,

37:37.170 --> 37:39.460
can you check on him
in the morning?

37:39.460 --> 37:41.960
Sure. Can I get you
a drink or anything?

37:41.960 --> 37:43.620
Oh, I've had too many.

37:43.620 --> 37:45.460
Well, come in, anyway. There's
something I want to show you.

37:49.170 --> 37:53.170
♪♪

37:53.170 --> 37:56.620
Look. We do
look good together.

37:56.620 --> 37:58.960
You know where else
we'd look good together?

37:58.960 --> 38:00.380
On the dance floor.

38:00.380 --> 38:02.290
Why do you want to go
to this wedding so much?

38:02.290 --> 38:03.420
Everyone likes
a good party.

38:03.420 --> 38:06.000
[ Laughs ]
I don't even know you.

38:06.000 --> 38:07.250
Get to know me
at the wedding.

38:09.120 --> 38:11.960
[ Laughing ] Okay.

38:11.960 --> 38:13.620
What are you doing?

38:13.620 --> 38:14.750
I'm sorry?

38:14.750 --> 38:17.620
This.
The smile and...

38:17.620 --> 38:19.170
inviting yourself
to be my date.

38:19.170 --> 38:22.580
[ Chuckles ]
You knocked on my door.

38:22.580 --> 38:24.290
Are you
hitting on me?

38:24.290 --> 38:25.830
I don't know
how to answer that.

38:25.830 --> 38:27.210
How about
with the truth?

38:27.210 --> 38:28.500
The truth?

38:28.500 --> 38:31.540
You intimidate me,
you're incredibly smart,

38:31.540 --> 38:33.960
and I know I don't have
to tell you this, but...

38:33.960 --> 38:35.670
you're damn
gorgeous, too.

38:35.670 --> 38:37.460
And I know you maybe
have a crush on Tegan.

38:37.460 --> 38:40.460
Th-That's just
what everyone says.

38:40.460 --> 38:43.880
Either way, anyone who doesn't
realize how great you are

38:43.880 --> 38:45.080
is not
paying attention.

38:47.170 --> 38:48.830
Thank you
for saying that.

38:51.920 --> 38:53.540
Uh...
[ Exhales sharply ]

38:53.540 --> 38:55.420
Mnh, um.

38:55.420 --> 38:58.080
We can't.
Why?

38:58.080 --> 39:01.960
Because I'm...
"fabstinent."

39:01.960 --> 39:03.540
I don't know
what that means.

39:03.540 --> 39:06.330
Oh, God.

39:06.330 --> 39:07.710
It means nothing.

39:07.710 --> 39:15.000
♪♪

39:15.000 --> 39:22.330
♪♪

39:22.330 --> 39:24.170
You don't
have to check on me.

39:24.170 --> 39:25.210
I'm not.

39:28.580 --> 39:31.880
I got my job at
Caplan & Gold back tonight.

39:31.880 --> 39:33.210
How?

39:34.750 --> 39:36.830
I begged.

39:36.830 --> 39:38.210
It's the only way
to keep fighting.
Stop.

39:38.210 --> 39:39.460
Governor
can't get away with --

39:39.460 --> 39:40.920
Enough, Annalise!

39:43.830 --> 39:46.040
It's my fault
he's dead, Nate.

39:47.250 --> 39:49.330
What?

39:49.330 --> 39:52.330
It was the Governor's plan
all along.

39:54.420 --> 39:58.290
Agree to pardon him,
get me on her side,

39:58.290 --> 40:00.170
and then
she had him killed.

40:07.290 --> 40:08.580
I know you hate me.

40:11.880 --> 40:13.290
I hate me.

40:15.250 --> 40:17.330
But I'm gonna
keep fighting.

40:17.330 --> 40:19.290
Even when she
comes after me next,

40:19.290 --> 40:20.880
it's the only way
to make it right.

40:20.880 --> 40:21.880
No.
Listen.

40:21.880 --> 40:24.210
I know it's her, Nate.

40:26.670 --> 40:28.580
I mean, you're not
fighting this alone.

40:33.120 --> 40:34.880
We're gonna
make her suffer.

40:34.880 --> 40:43.710
♪♪

40:43.710 --> 40:45.710
What the hell
did I tell you?

40:45.710 --> 40:48.000
This is exactly
what I said would happen.

40:48.000 --> 40:50.250
Gabriel is playing us,
just like I said,

40:50.250 --> 40:52.620
so you need to tell Annalise
who he is already.

40:52.620 --> 40:54.330
She's not in a place
to hear this right now.

40:54.330 --> 40:56.830
Okay, if you don't tell her,
then I will.

40:56.830 --> 40:58.210
Bonnie: Tell her what?

40:58.210 --> 41:04.000
♪♪

41:04.000 --> 41:10.210
♪♪

41:10.210 --> 41:11.540
[ Indistinct conversations ]

41:11.540 --> 41:14.670
♪♪

41:14.670 --> 41:16.540
[ Baby crying ]

41:16.540 --> 41:23.500
♪♪

41:23.500 --> 41:30.210
♪♪

41:30.210 --> 41:31.920
[ Breathing heavily ]

41:31.920 --> 41:33.540
[ Crying continues ]

41:33.540 --> 41:37.330
♪♪

41:37.330 --> 41:40.920
[ Breathlessly ]
Listen to me real close.

41:40.920 --> 41:44.380
Take his car and him
and drive away.

41:44.380 --> 41:45.540
[ Baby crying ]

41:45.540 --> 41:47.040
We can figure out
the rest later.

41:47.040 --> 41:49.380
Just do whatever you need to

41:49.380 --> 41:50.750
to get yourself together.

41:50.750 --> 41:52.210
I know you can.

41:52.210 --> 41:53.670
I'll take care
of everything.

41:55.080 --> 41:58.080
Just trust me.
[ Breathes sharply ]

42:08.420 --> 42:15.460
♪♪

